cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with emotion recognition in speech using generative models, which falls under the sub-category of Speech and Dialogue Processing (cs.SD). However, the paper also uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for modeling distributions, which is a popular technique in the fields of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language understanding (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes different metrics to measure the performance of GAN models, which falls under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also performs a cross-corpus study to study the utility of synthetic samples in low resource conditions, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
